description._content: Collection: NASA Image eXchange Collection Title: Aerials - NACA buildings Description: Full Scale Wind Tunnel and Tow Basin under construction. L4496 caption: "The Langley complex as seen in May 1930. Under construction in foreground is the Full Scale Wind Tunnel." Photograph and caption published in Winds of Change, 75th Anniversary NASA publication (page 3), by James Schultz. Date: 06.12.1930 Credit: NASA Langley Research Center (NASA-LaRC) [ lisar.larc.nasa.gov/ ] ID: EL-2001-00455 Other ID: L4496 UID: SPD-NIX-EL-2001-0045 5 Orignial url: nix.ksc.nasa.gov/info?id=EL-2001-00455&orgid=1 SOURCE: nasaimages.org/luna/servlet/detail/nasaNAS~2~2~5443~107065: Visit www.nasaimages.org for the most comprehensive compilation of NASA stills, film and video, created in partnership with Internet Archive.
